        <h2 class="title"><a href="/australia-photo-log-now-available">Australia photo-log now available</a></h2>    <span class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="/user/brad" title="View user profile." rel="nofollow">brad</a> on Thu, 2005-11-10 02:42.</span>
    <span class="taxonomy"><ul class="links inline"><li class="first last taxonomy_term_1"><a href="/archives/cat_photography.html" rel="tag" title="" class="taxonomy_term_1">Photography</a></li>
</ul></span>
    <div class="content"><p><a href=http://pic.templetons.com/brad/photo/australia><img src=http://pic.templetons.com/brad/photo/australia/yellow/thumb/IMG_6230.JPG class=blogpic></a>
Earlier I posted about my panoramas of Australia.  Now I have put up the large gallery of
regular spect photos from the trip.   We began with a short visit to Melbourne, then drove the Great Ocean Road , ending in Adelaide.   From there we flew to Darwin in the top end to visit Kakadu National Park and Litchfield National Park. </p>

<p>Then it was on to Cairns and the Great Barrier Reef, and finally ending in Syndey for the AUUG conference.  We took almost 3000 photos &#8212; the galleries contain the best 250 or so, along with captions and some stories.   It&#8217;s freshly up, and may need a bit of proofing and refinement, but feel free to enjoy.  Thanks again to my hosts and other great folks from Australia.</p>

<p>Visit the <a href="http://pic.templetons.com/brad/photo/australia">Photos of Australia</a>.</p>

<p>At right: Saltie Crocodile catches a meal at sunrise in the outback.</p>
</div>
